# 🛍️ E-Commerce Admin Dashboard

This is a web-based E-Commerce Admin Dashboard built using **PHP**, **MySQL**, **HTML/CSS/JS**, and modern frontend techniques. The application allows administrators to manage users, products, and view orders efficiently.

---

## 📁 Project Structure

/final_project/
│
├── Admin/
│ ├── get_all_users.php
│ ├── edit_user.php
│ ├── add_new_product.php
│ └── ...other admin pages
│
├── APIs/
│ ├── UsersAPI.php
│ ├── ProductsAPI.php
│ └── OrdersAPI.php
│
├── js/
│ ├── EditAll.js
│ └── ...JS files for validation and interaction
│
├── css/
│ └── styles.css
│
├── Home.php
├── dbConnection.php
└── README.md

---

## ⚙️ Technologies Used

- **PHP** (vanilla backend and APIs)
- **MySQL** (database)
- **HTML5 / CSS3**
- **JavaScript (Vanilla)** – client-side validation, dynamic UI
- **RESTful API** pattern
- **Session Management** – login, role-based access

---

## 🚀 Features

- ✅ Admin/User login & session validation
- ✅ View all users and orders
- ✅ Add, edit, delete products
- ✅ Role-based access control (admin vs customer)
- ✅ Client-side and server-side validation
- ✅ JSON API consumption using `fetch()`

---

## 🔐 Role-Based Access

| Role     | Access                                       |
|----------|----------------------------------------------|
| Admin    | Full access to manage users/products/orders  |
| Customer | Redirected to home page                      |

---

## 🧪 How to Run Locally

1. **Clone the Repository:**

```bash
git clone https://github.com/AhmedIsmailE/E-Commerce.git
Set Up Apache & MySQL

Use XAMPP or Laragon

Place the repo inside your htdocs or www directory.

Import Database

Open phpMyAdmin

Import the .sql dump (usually located in /db.sql or shared separately)

Update API URLs (if needed):

In your API calls, ensure they point to:
http://localhost/NTI/final_project/APIs/...
Or update based on your folder name/path.

And Makesure your database in Mysql is same as projectdb
And for using different account in mySQL you have to update it in dbconnection.php file
